[Baby Crying]

955
00:57:17,590 --> 00:57:18,960
艾莉丝!
Iris. Cole.

956
00:57:19,040 --> 00:57:21,120
柯尔!

957
00:57:22,590 --> 00:57:24,910
游行好玩吗?
Was that fun or what?

958
00:57:25,010 --> 00:57:27,170
柯尔有点不太对劲
There's something wrong with Cole.

959
00:57:27,970 --> 00:57:31,250
-怎样? -不知道,但我用尽办法
I don't know, but I've... I've tried different things.

960
00:57:31,390 --> 00:57:36,550
从背后吓他…敲锅子,大声喊他名字…

961
00:57:33,176 --> 00:57:36,384
Um, sneaking up behind him and...

962
00:57:36,690 --> 00:57:39,310
跺脚
banging pots and screaming his name and stomping on the floor.

963
00:57:39,440 --> 00:57:42,970
我跺脚他才回头.咧嘴笑,以为我在跟他玩
He... He turned when I did that. Big smile.

964
00:57:43,110 --> 00:57:45,150
艾莉丝
- He thought I was playing a game. - Iris.

965
00:57:46,650 --> 00:57:49,320
我猜他听不见
I don't think he can hear.

966
00:58:02,250 --> 00:58:03,530
柯尔!
Cole?

967
00:58:06,420 --> 00:58:07,790
柯尔?
[Clapping] Cole?

968
00:58:11,840 --> 00:58:14,080
柯尔?

969
00:58:13,534 --> 00:58:16,117
Cole! [Clapping]

970
00:58:15,760 --> 00:58:17,840
柯尔?
Cole? [Clapping]

971
00:58:22,310 --> 00:58:25,350
柯尔有90%听力受损
Cole has a 90% hearing loss.

972
00:58:25,440 --> 00:58:28,890
如果加以训练 他会学会利用那仅剩余的听力
Now, with training he will learn to use what hearing he has left.

973
00:58:29,030 --> 00:58:33,070
像对正常小孩一样待他 即使他听不见也要跟他讲话

974
00:58:30,711 --> 00:58:34,754
Treat him as if he's normal. Talk to him as if he can hear you.

975
00:58:33,200 --> 00:58:36,890
我注意到柯尔习惯用手势来表达

976
00:58:34,755 --> 00:58:38,464
I notice Cole uses gestures to help himself be understood.

977
00:58:36,990 --> 00:58:41,040
我提醒你们不要用手势来回应

978
00:58:38,508 --> 00:58:42,300
Let me caution you, don't use them back.

979
00:58:41,120 --> 00:58:44,900
手势表达无助于帮他立足社会
Gestures won't help him find his place in a hearing world.

980
00:58:45,000 --> 00:58:50,120
等他大一点,有专门学校教他讲话
When he's older, there are schools that will help him and you to find his voice.

981
00:58:51,000 --> 00:58:56,120
（贝多芬"A大调第七交响曲"）

982
00:58:53,183 --> 00:58:57,726
[Beethoven: "Symphony No. 7 In A Major"]

983
00:59:03,810 --> 00:59:05,880
他听不见

984
00:59:06,560 --> 00:59:12,180
芸芸众生之中,偏偏是他 一点都听不见
He couldn't hear.

985
00:59:08,400 --> 00:59:10,942
Of all people.

986
00:59:10,943 --> 00:59:13,485
Not a thing.

987
00:59:12,690 --> 00:59:15,060
正因为贝多芬听不见
And because Beethoven couldn't hear, the thought of him conducting...

988
00:59:15,190 --> 00:59:22,740
绝大多数人都认为他的指挥或作曲...乏善可陈

989
00:59:19,364 --> 00:59:24,491
or let alone composing... was pathetic to most people.

990
00:59:22,780 --> 00:59:27,280
为了回应这些人 他谱写了第七交响乐,并指挥公演

991
00:59:24,493 --> 00:59:29,828
And so to answer them, he composed and conducted the "Seventh Symphony. "

992
00:59:29,829 --> 00:59:31,703
[Continues]

993
00:59:31,540 --> 00:59:34,000
想想看…
Just try to imagine...

994
00:59:34,130 --> 00:59:36,530
贝多芬站在指挥台上…
Beethoven standing on that podium...

995
00:59:38,130 --> 00:59:40,210
手执指挥棒…
holding his baton...

996
00:59:40,930 --> 00:59:44,420
优雅地挥舞着双手…
his hands waving gracefully through the air...

997
00:59:46,060 --> 00:59:51,010
心中的乐团正完美地演出

998
00:59:47,590 --> 00:59:50,632
and the orchestra in his mind...

999
00:59:50,633 --> 00:59:53,092
is playing perfectly.

1000
00:59:53,940 --> 00:59:59,280
而他面前的乐团…却拚命地在跟上他的节拍
And the orchestra in front of him...

1001
00:59:58,596 --> 01:00:01,888
trying desperately just to keep up.

1002
01:00:04,490 --> 01:00:06,860
还有个故事…
[Clicks Tongue] There is a story...

1003
01:00:08,080 --> 01:00:11,440
为了创作…

1004
01:00:09,603 --> 01:00:12,937
that in order to write his music...

1005
01:00:11,540 --> 01:00:14,900
贝多芬断然锯掉钢琴脚
Beethoven literally sawed the legs off his piano...

1006
01:00:15,000 --> 01:00:18,120
使琴身贴在地板上

1007
01:00:16,858 --> 01:00:20,775
so that he could lay the body flat on the ground.

1008
01:00:19,630 --> 01:00:21,700
然后…
And then...

